                        "content": "A client with gastrointestinal hypermotility has a prescription to receive atropine sulfate. The nurse would withhold the medication and question the prescription if the client has a history of which disease process?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nAtropine sulfate can cause a blockade of muscarinic receptors on the iris sphincter, producing mydriasis (dilation of the pupils). It also produces cycloplegia (relaxation of the ciliary muscles). It is contraindicated in clients with narrow-angle glaucoma. The other options are therapeutic reasons for using the medication.",
                        "id": "5b66d4567b5247428f90e96edacfbefe",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
