                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nRifaximin may be prescribed for the client with portosystemic encephalopathy. It is a broad-spectrum antibiotic that destroys normal bacteria found in the bowel, thereby decreasing protein breakdown and ammonia production. The remaining options are not accurate rationales for administration of this medication to this client.\n",
